call = {"id":444,"key":"Gladius","title":"Gladius","latest":{"id":186964,"timestamp":"2021-10-28T08:30:53Z"},"content_model":"wikitext","license":{"url":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/","title":"Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike"},"source":"{{Infobox vehicle\n| image                           = Gladius - Flying away from world through debris.jpg\n| name                            = Gladius\n| rsistoreurl                     = https://robertsspaceindustries.com/pledge/ships/gladius/Gladius\n| manufacturer                    = AEGS\n| role                            = Light Fighter\n| size                            = Small\n| mincrew                         = 1\n| maxcrew                         = 1\n| series                          = Gladius\n| cargocapacity                   = 0\n| productionstate                 = Flight ready\n| productionstatedesc             = Flyable release [[Star Citizen Patch V1.1.0]]\n| loanervehicle                   = \n| buycost                         = 1169900\n| rentcost                        = \n| rentcostac                      = \n| claimtime                       = 10:07\n| expeditetime                    = 1:41\n| expeditecost                    = 2535\n| pledgeavailability              = Always available\n| pledgecost                      = 90\n| originalpledgecost              = 80\n| warbondcost                     = \n| originalwarbondcost             = \n| length                          = 20\n| beam                            = 17\n| height                          = 5.5\n| combatspeed                     = 208\n| maxspeed                        = 1236\n| mass                            = 51352\n| releasedate                     = {{SDA|sctime=yes|2579}}\n| retiredate                      = \n| developedfrom                   = Stilleto\n| developedinto                   = Arrow\n| galactapediaurl                 = https://robertsspaceindustries.com/galactapedia/article/0j46NP5eB3-gladius\n| presentationurl                 = https://robertsspaceindustries.com/comm-link/transmission/14008-Aegis-Gladius-Declassified\n| brochureurl                     = https://robertsspaceindustries.com/media/1wsqdbmlau8grr/source/Gladius-Brochure-V7.pdf\n| trailerurl                      = https://youtu.be/IBIFpEPl8kk\n}}\n\nThe [[Aegis Dynamics|Aegis]] P5G '''Gladius''' is a light fighter of an older design which has been updated over the years to keep up with modern technology. In military circles, the Gladius is beloved for its performance and its simplicity. A fast, light fighter with a laser-focus on dogfighting, the Gladius is an ideal interceptor or escort ship.<ref>{{Cite RSI|url=pledge/ships/gladius/Gladius|text=Gladius - Ship Page}}</ref>\n\n<blockquote>Contact with the enemy means that your craft will be taking fire. Though the experience can be har-\nrowing for new pilots, understand that the Gladius light fighter offers considerable defensive systems to protect the operator and keep the craft flying.</blockquote>\n\n==Specifications==\n<tabber>\nAvionics & Systems=\n{{Vehicle avionics\n| radarcount = 1\n| computercount = 1\n\n| radar1quantity = 1\n| radar1size = 1\n| radar1manufacturer = GRNP\n| radar1name = [[Ecouter]]\n\n| computer1quantity = 1\n| computer1size = 1\n| computer1manufacturer = BEHR\n| computer1name = [[CSR-RP]]\n}}\n{{Vehicle systems\n| powerplantcount = 1\n| batterycount = 1\n| coolercount = 1\n| shieldgeneratorcount = 1\n| lifesupportcount = 1\n\n| powerplant1quantity = 1\n| powerplant1size = 1\n| powerplant1manufacturer = AEGS\n| powerplant1name = [[Regulus]]\n\n| battery1quantity = 1\n| battery1size = 1\n| battery1manufacturer = AMRS\n| battery1name = [[FortCell]]\n\n| cooler1quantity = 2\n| cooler1size = 1\n| cooler1manufacturer = AEGS\n| cooler1name = [[Bracer]]\n\n| shieldgenerator1quantity = 2\n| shieldgenerator1size = 1\n| shieldgenerator1manufacturer = GODI\n| shieldgenerator1name = [[AllStop]]\n\n| lifesupport1quantity = 1\n| lifesupport1size = 1\n| lifesupport1manufacturer = TBD\n| lifesupport1name = S Life Support\n}}\n|-|\nPropulsion & Thrusters=\n{{Vehicle propulsion\n| fuelintakecount = 1\n| fueltankcount = 1\n| quantumdrivecount = 1\n| jumpdrivecount = 1\n| quantumfueltankcount = 1\n| fuelintake1quantity = 2\n| fuelintake1size = 1\n| fuelintake1manufacturer = \n| fuelintake1name = S Fuel Intake\n| fueltank1quantity = 2\n| fueltank1size = 1\n| fueltank1manufacturer = \n| fueltank1name = S Fuel Tank\n| quantumdrive1quantity = 1\n| quantumdrive1size = 1\n| quantumdrive1manufacturer = WETK\n| quantumdrive1name = [[Beacon (quantum drive)|Beacon]]\n| jumpdrive1quantity = 1\n| jumpdrive1size = 1\n| jumpdrive1manufacturer = \n| jumpdrive1name = S Jump Module\n| quantumfueltank1quantity = 1\n| quantumfueltank1size = 1\n| quantumfueltank1manufacturer = \n| quantumfueltank1name = S Quantum Fuel Tank\n}}\n{{Vehicle thrusters\n| mainthrustercount = 1\n| maneuveringthrustercount = 3\n| mainthruster1quantity = 2\n| mainthruster1size = 3\n| mainthruster1manufacturer = DSTC\n| mainthruster1name = [[STC Blue]]\n| maneuveringthruster1quantity = 2\n| maneuveringthruster1size = 3\n| maneuveringthruster1manufacturer = \n| maneuveringthruster1name = Retro Thruster\n| maneuveringthruster2quantity = 4\n| maneuveringthruster2size = 2\n| maneuveringthruster2manufacturer = AEGS\n| maneuveringthruster2name = [[Winnowing D1 Omni]]\n| maneuveringthruster3quantity = 4\n| maneuveringthruster3size = 2\n| maneuveringthruster3manufacturer = AEGS\n| maneuveringthruster3name = [[Winnowing D1 Rotational]]\n}}\n|-|\nWeaponry=\n{{Vehicle weaponry\n| weaponcount = 2\n| turretcount = 0\n| missilerackcount = 2\n| utilityitemcount = 2\n\n| weapon1quantity = 1\n| weapon1size = 3\n| weapon1manufacturer = GATS\n| weapon1name = [[Mantis GT-220]]\n\n| missilerack1quantity = 2\n| missilerack1size = 3\n| missilerack1manufacturer = BEHR\n| missilerack1name = [[MSD-322 Missile Rack]]\n| missilerack1missilecount = 1\n| missilerack1missile1quantity = 4\n| missilerack1missile1size = 2\n| missilerack1missile1manufacturer = FSKI\n| missilerack1missile1name = [[Ignite II]]\n\n| weapon2quantity = 2\n| weapon2size = 3\n| weapon2manufacturer = KLWE\n| weapon2name = [[CF-337 Panther Repeater]]\n\n| missilerack2quantity = 2\n| missilerack2size = 3\n| missilerack2manufacturer = BEHR\n| missilerack2name = [[MSD-313 Missile Rack]]\n| missilerack2missilecount = 1\n| missilerack2missile1quantity = 2\n| missilerack2missile1size = 3\n| missilerack2missile1manufacturer = FSKI\n| missilerack2missile1name = [[Arrester III]]\n\n| utilityitem1quantity = 1\n| utilityitem1size = 1\n| utilityitem1manufacturer = \n| utilityitem1name = Noise Launcher\n\n| utilityitem2quantity = 1\n| utilityitem2size = 1\n| utilityitem2manufacturer = \n| utilityitem2name = Decoy Launcher\n}}\n</tabber>\n\n==History==\n\n===Development===\nThe Gladius was developed in the 26th century by [[Aegis Dynamics]] to replace the [[Stiletto|Stiletto interceptors]]. It was first deployed in the [[First Tevarin War]].<ref>Jump Point September 2014</ref>\n\n===Declassification===\nIn [[2944]], with some Gladius squadrons converting to the wider deployment of the [[F7A Hornet]] and the introduction of the [[F8 Lightning]] to elite units, the [[UEE Navy|Navy]] has begun to auction older Gladius to planetary governments and qualified mercenaries. The spacecraft available to civilians are retired military models, with the same specifications and upgrade potential. Classified weapons technologies have been removed from the spaceframes, but they can be outfitted with a variety of civilian-grade weapons. The decommissioning process has also made room for [[civilian]] standard upgrades such as [[Jump Drive|jump drives]].<ref>{{Cite RSI|url=comm-link/transmission/14008-Aegis-Gladius-Declassified|text=Aegis Gladius Declassified!}}</ref>\n\n==Model==\n\n===Ship profile===\n\n<tabber>\n In space=\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Isometric\n!Above\n!Port-side\n!Front\n!Rear\n!Below\n|-\n|[[File:Gladius_in_space_-_Isometric.jpg|center|frameless|100x67px]]\n|[[File:Gladius_in_space_-_Above.jpg|center|frameless|100x67px]]\n|[[File:Gladius_in_space_-_Port.jpg|center|frameless|100x67px]]\n|[[File:Gladius_in_space_-_Front.jpg|center|frameless|100x67px]]\n|[[File:Gladius_in_space_-_Rear.jpg|center|frameless|100x67px]]\n|[[File:Gladius_in_space_-_Below.jpg|center|frameless|100x67px]]\n|}\n|-|\n Hangar=\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Isometric\n!Above\n!Port-side\n!Front\n!Rear\n|-\n|[[File:Gladius_in_SelfLand_-_Isometric.jpg|center|frameless|100x67px]]\n|[[File:Gladius_in_SelfLand_-_Above.jpg|center|frameless|100x67px]]\n|[[File:Gladius_in_SelfLand_-_Port.jpg|center|frameless|100x67px]]\n|[[File:Gladius_in_SelfLand_-_Front.jpg|center|frameless|100x67px]]\n|[[File:Gladius_in_SelfLand_-_Rear.jpg|center|frameless|100x67px]]\n|}\n</tabber>\n\n===Special edition===\n{{for|more information|:Category:Gladius series#Special Editions}}\n\n'''Gladius \"Valiant\"'''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|[[File:Gladius Valiant in space - Isometric.jpg|center|frameless|100x67px]]\n|Created as part of the [[Masters of Flight]] series in conjunction with the flight-sim [[Arena Commander]], it pays tribute to famed defense pilot [[Condi Hillard]] for being the first [[Human]] on record to defeat a [[Vanduul]] in combat.<ref name=\"Valiant\">{{Cite RSI|url=pledge/ships/gladius/Gladius-Valiant|text=Gladius \"Valiant\" Ship Page}}</ref>\n|}\n\n'''Gladius \"Pirate\"'''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|[[File:Gladius Pirate in space - Isometric.jpg|center|frameless|100x67px]]\n|With a red and black pirate livery, it's only available when defeating \"Pirate Swarm\" in [[Arena Commander]].<ref name=\"Pirate-Gladius\">{{Cite RSI|url=pledge/ships/gladius/Pirate-Gladius|text=Gladius \"Pirate\" Ship Page}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Paints===\n{{for|more information|:Category:Gladius series#Paints}}\nThe following paints (skins) can be used on all Gladius variants.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Image\n!Paint Name\n!Description\n!Price (aUEC)\n!Price ($)\n|-\n|[[File:Gladius Frostbite in space - Isometric.jpg|center|frameless|100x67px]]\n|\"Frostbite\"\n|Blueish white colour with grey/black camo pattern and dark grey accents.\n|[not available]\n|7.00\n|-\n|[[File:Gladius Invictus BG in space - Isometric.jpg|center|frameless|100x67px]]\n|\"Invictus Blue & Gold\"\n|Blue colour with dark grey & gold accents and a Invictus logo.\n|[not available]\n|7.00\n|-\n|[[File:Gladius Timberline in space - Isometric.jpg|center|frameless|100x67px]]\n|\"Timberline\"\n|Olive green colour with orange and dark olive green accents.\n|[not available]\n|4.50\n|}\n\n==In-game availability & pricing==\n{{Note|'''Updated''': {{Start date and age|2021|05|06|p=yes}} - [[Star Citizen Alpha 3.13.0|Alpha 3.13.0]]}}\n\n===Buying===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n![[New Deal]], Lorville\n![[Astro Armada]], Area18\n|-\n|1,169,900\n|Unavailable\n|}\n\n===Renting===\n''Unavailable''\n\n''Prices given are per-day. Prices for all rental periods can be found at [[Ship renting]].''\n\n==Pledge price history==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Date\n!Pledge cost (USD)\n!Insurance\n!Availability\n!Sale\n|-\n|2020-05-26\n|90\n|120 months\n|Time-limited\n|Invictus 2950 <ref>{{Cite RSI|url=comm-link/transmission/17595-Invictus-2950|text=Invictus 2950 Sale}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Gallery==\n<tabber>\n Official=\n{{gallery\n|Gladius_-_Take_off.jpg\n|Ship-gladius-backfly.jpg\n|Ship-gladius-backtakeoff.jpg\n|Gladius_with_Hornet_attacking_Mustangs.jpg\n|Neil-mcknight-gladius-003.jpg\n|Gladius_Front_Ortho.jpg\n|Gladiuscover.jpg\n|Gladius_Front.jpg\n|Gladius_Rear.jpg\n|Gladius Store Beauty.jpg\n|Ship-Gladius-Cockpit 02 N.jpg\n|Ship-gladius-cockpit.jpg\n}}\n|-|\n In-game=\n{{gallery\n|Gladius Ingame Missed.png\n|Ship-gladius-tophangar.jpg\n|Gladius Hangar 3.1.png\n|Star Citizen- Space Brrrrrt.png\n|Gladius_flying_in_space_-_Above.png\n|Gladius_in_the_shadow.jpg\n|Gladius_flying_in_space_-_Rear_Above.jpg\n}}\n|-|\n 'Valiant'=\n{{gallery\n|Gladius Valiant in space - Isometric.jpg\n|Gladius Valiant in space - Above.jpg\n|Gladius Valiant in space - Port.jpg\n|Gladius Valiant in space - Front.jpg\n|Gladius Valiant in space - Rear.jpg\n|Gladius Valiant in space - Below.jpg\n|Gladius_Valiants_x2_flying_in_formation.jpg\n|Gladius_Valiant_in_Idris_bay_-_Front_Above.jpg\n|Gladius_Valiants_x3_flying_in_formation.jpg\n|Gladius_Valiant_in_Lorville_hangar.png\n|GladiusValiant.jpg\n|Gladius_Valiant_in_SelfLand_-_Isometric.jpg\n|Gladius_Valiant_in_SelfLand_-_Above.jpg\n|Gladius_Valiant_in_SelfLand_-_Port.jpg\n|Gladius_Valiant_in_SelfLand_-_Front.jpg\n|Gladius_Valiant_in_SelfLand_-_Rear.jpg\n|Gladius Valiant Take Off.png\n|Gladius Valiant Engine.png\n|Gladius Valiant Back.png\n|Gladius Valiant 2.6.3 02.jpg\n|Gladius Valiant 2.6.3 03.jpg\n|Gladius Valiant 2.6.3 01.jpg\n|Gladius Valiant 2.6.3 04.jpg\n|Gladius Valiant Glenn 2.6.3.jpg\n}}\n|-|\n 'Pirate'=\n{{gallery\n|Gladius Pirate in space - Isometric.jpg\n|Gladius Pirate in space - Above.jpg\n|Gladius Pirate in space - Port.jpg\n|Gladius Pirate in space - Front.jpg\n|Gladius Pirate in space - Rear.jpg\n|Gladius Pirate in space - Below.jpg\n|Gladius_Pirate_flying_over_Celin.png\n|Gladius_Pirate_and_Catapillar_Pirate_-_Dying_Star_flying_away.jpg\n|Gladius_Pirate_x5_-_Attacking_station_over_world.jpg\n|Gladius_Pirate_in_SelfLand_-_Isometric.jpg\n|Gladius_Pirate_in_SelfLand_-_Above.jpg\n|Gladius_Pirate_in_SelfLand_-_Port.jpg\n|Gladius_Pirate_in_SelfLand_-_Front.jpg\n|Gladius_Pirate_in_SelfLand_-_Rear.jpg\n}}\n|-|\n Official Paints=\n{{gallery\n|Gladius_Frostbite_-_Landed.jpg\n|Gladius_Invictus_Blue_and_Gold_-_Landed.jpg\n|Gladius_Timberline_-_Landed.jpg\n}}\n</tabber>\n\n==Development==\nThe Gladius was designed by [[Gavin Rothery]] (Freelance Conceptist)<ref>[http://www.gavinrothery.com/820-park/ Gavin Rothery: Star Citizen Hardware and Ship Design]</ref> and directed by [[Paul Jones]]. Other contributors include [[Foundry 42|Foundry 42]]'s [[Bjorn Seinstra]] (Lead Vehicle Artist), [[Phill Meller]] (Lead Designer), [[Neil McKnight]] (Senior 3D Artist), along with [[Chris Roberts]].<ref>{{Cite RSI|url=comm-link/engineering/14273-WIP-Gladius|text=Comm-Link - WIP: Gladius}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2017, the Gladius received a cockpit rework to accompany the new [[item 2.0]] system. The center monitor is removed to provide better visibility for the front turret. The side monitors are enlarged to show additional information. The cockpit reworked is deployed in [[Star Citizen Alpha 3.0.0]].<ref>{{Cite RSI|url=comm-link/transmission/15955-Around-The-Verse|text=Around the Verse - Upgrading Ships to Item 2.0, Part 2|trx=around-the-verse-upgrading-ships-to-item-2-0-part-2}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2021, the gold standard Gladius is released to the [[Persistent Universe]] in [[Star Citizen Alpha 3.13.0|Alpha 3.13]]. That includes many level of detail, decal, geometry, material, and paint changes inside the cockpit and on the exterior of the ship. Noticeably, the update implements the exterior access points to the physicalized components, as well as personal locker, fuel port access, and numerous maintenance panels.<ref>{{Cite RSI|url=https://robertsspaceindustries.com/spectrum/community/SC/forum/190048/thread/star-citizen-alpha-3-13-0-ptu-7240320-patch-notes|text=Star Citizen Alpha 3.13.0 PTU Patch Notes|accessdate=2021-04-06}}</ref><ref name=\"ingame3130\">In-game survey in Alpha 3.13</ref>\n\n==See also==\n\n*[[Gladius Valiant]]: A dogfighting variant with a custom loadout and livery as part of the [[Masters of Flight]] series\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Navplate manufacturers|AEGS}}\n{{Navplate vehicles}}\n\n[[Category:Referral rewards]]"}
